{{Infobox officeholder | name = John Butrovich | image = File:John Butrovich.jpg | state_senate = Alaska | party = [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] | office1 = | birth_name = John Butrovich Jr. | birth_date = {{birth date|1910|3|22}} | birth_place = [[Fairbanks, Alaska|Fairbanks]], [[Territory of Alaska]], U.S. | death_date = {{death date and age|1997|6|3|1910|3|22}} | death_place = [[Fairbanks, Alaska]], U.S. | education = [[Washington State University]] | term_start1 = 1963 | term_end1 = 1979 }}
'''John Butrovich Jr.''' (March 22, 1910 — June 3, 1997) was an American businessman and politician.
Born in a mining camp near [[Fairbanks, Alaska]] to a [[Montenegrin American]] family, Butrovich graduated from Fairbanks High School in 1929. He then went to [[Washington State University]]. He returned to Fairbanks and was in the insurance business. From 1944 to 1958, Butrovich served in the Alaska Territorial Senate and was a [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]. In 1958, Butrovich ran in the [[Alaska gubernatorial election, 1958|election]] for [[Governor of Alaska]] and lost the election. From 1963 to 1979, Butrovich served in the [[Alaska State Senate]]. Butrovich died at his home in Fairbanks, Alaska from a long illness.<ref>[http://www.ourcampaigns.com/CandidateDetail.html?CandidateID=53701 OurCampaigns.com.-John Butrovich, Jr.]</ref><ref>'Alaska Statehood Leader John Butrovich Dies at 87,' '''Sikta Daily Sentinel,''' June 4, 1997, pg. 3</ref>
